Nmore dats..

725429f-a.text:
52nd Street (foreground, formerly Dickison Street, also Woodside Ave.), adjoininm the S.W. corner of 39th Ave. (parallel to front of this house; formerly Middleburg Ave. and also known as Dutch Eills Road.), showing a rear view of the John Morrell house. See other views for more

725430f-b.text:
(1)
52nd Street (foreground, formerly Dickison Street, also Woodside Ave.), adjoining the S.W. corner of 39th Ave. (front of this house; formerly Middleburg Ave. and also Dutch Kills Road), showing a rear view of the John Morrell house, which was destroyed by fire in November 1925. It was erected in the middle of the 18th Century by John Morrell who erected a house and a smithy (forge), on the estate of His father-in-law. John Alburtes. Other owners were John Morrell 1779, John W. Morrell 1852-1860, William Morrell, and Wm. Morgenthaler of New York in 1903.
1922.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing a more extensive view. At the extreme left is a house located at the B.E. corner of the first mentioned location,
and situated in the old town of Newtown.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
